WEBVTT

00:02.211 --> 00:05.214
GREAT DRAGON:
In a land of myth and a time of magic...

00:05.380 --> 00:10.677
...the destiny of a great kingdom
rests on the shoulders of a young man.

00:10.844 --> 00:13.555
His name: Merlin.

00:16.892 --> 00:20.354
All right. Who drank all my water?

00:20.521 --> 00:21.980
[BELCHES]

00:22.147 --> 00:24.691
- I believe you have your answer.
-You said I could have some.

00:24.858 --> 00:28.320
| said you could have some.
| didn't say you could drink every last drop.

00:28.487 --> 00:31.114
- I was thirsty.
-Here. Have some of mine.

00:33.617 --> 00:35.035
[ALL LAUGHING]

00:35.202 --> 00:36.703
-That's very funny.
-Here.

00:36.870 --> 00:38.914
Unlike these ignorant fools,
| share with my friends.

00:42.209 --> 00:43.710
MAN:
Maybe I'll drink all of yours.

00:46.171 --> 00:48.298
[CHATTERING AND LAUGHING]

00:49.550 --> 00:50.592
Shh!

00:52.010 --> 00:53.512
What is it?

00:54.596 --> 00:57.808
| saw something in the trees. There.

01:16.118 --> 01:17.786
What is this place?

01:24.543 --> 01:26.253
This is a shrine.

01:26.962 --> 01:30.507
In the time of the old religion, they built shrines
like this to appease restless spirits.

01:30.674 --> 01:32.301
We shouldn't be here.

01:32.467 --> 01:33.802
[RUSTLING]

01:41.435 --> 01:42.644
Boo!

01:43.979 --> 01:45.355
MERLIN:
It isn't funny.

01:45.606 --> 01:48.275
Gaius told me about places like this,
and they're cursed.

01:50.110 --> 01:51.528
[WIND GUSTS]

02:00.912 --> 02:02.122
[SCREECHES]

02:03.415 --> 02:06.168
[CAWING]

02:06.335 --> 02:08.002
There's your spirit, Merlin.

02:09.670 --> 02:12.007
There's nothing here for us. Move out.

02:27.397 --> 02:28.940
[WATER TRICKLING]

03:00.138 --> 03:01.598
[SIGHS]

03:08.480 --> 03:10.399
[VOICES WHISPERING]

04:01.324 --> 04:03.243
You all right?

04:03.410 --> 04:05.120
What do you mean?

04:05.287 --> 04:07.497
You're very quiet.
You didn't say a word on the way home.

04:08.206 --> 04:10.834
It's called thinking, Merlin.
You should try it sometime.

04:11.001 --> 04:12.127
GWAINE:
Merlin.

04:14.588 --> 04:18.759
-What's that?
-Salt. Pour it in a circle at the foot of your bed.

04:18.925 --> 04:21.136
Helps to protect you from evil spirits.

04:21.303 --> 04:23.764
MERLIN: Really? Does that work?
GWAINE: Absolutely.

04:23.930 --> 04:27.225
And if it doesn't, Gaius can always
put it in his supper.

04:28.143 --> 04:29.728
Very funny.

04:32.355 --> 04:36.443
GAIUS: I'm surprised that such a shrine
exists so close to Camelot.

04:36.610 --> 04:38.695
And it was cursed.

04:38.862 --> 04:40.989
| could feel it.

04:42.365 --> 04:44.117
You were right to be wary.

04:44.409 --> 04:47.954
The druids built shrines to bring rest
to tormented souls.

04:48.121 --> 04:52.667
Souls that were so badly wronged,
they could find no peace in the other world.

04:52.834 --> 04:55.921
Why do they hang all the ribbons and flags?

04:56.963 --> 04:58.006
[GAIUS SIGHS]

04:58.173 --> 05:01.092
The ancient rituals heal the ground...

05:01.259 --> 05:03.720
...so that the souls of the victims
can find rest.

05:03.887 --> 05:09.601
But the magic that binds the earth
is delicate and is easily undone...

05:10.227 --> 05:15.565
...So the ribbons and flags act as a warning.

05:15.732 --> 05:17.442
Wish I'd known that earlier.

05:18.735 --> 05:20.987
Did anyone touch anything?

05:21.822 --> 05:24.533
Uh, no. I don't think so. Why? What is it?

05:25.909 --> 05:32.040
Anyone who disturbs the resting place
risks releasing the spirit.

05:32.999 --> 05:35.877
Merlin, you must promise me
you'll never return to that place.

05:36.044 --> 05:39.005
Oh, don't worry.
| have no intention of going back there.

05:40.173 --> 05:42.342
And for once, I'm not lying to you.

06:07.033 --> 06:08.618
[WATER DRIPPING]

06:12.330 --> 06:13.707
Hello?

06:15.667 --> 06:17.502
[WATER DRIPPING CONTINUES]

06:23.592 --> 06:24.718
Who's there?

06:41.443 --> 06:43.111
Show yourself.

06:43.278 --> 06:45.488
[WATER DRIPPING STOPS]

07:19.773 --> 07:21.066
[GASPS]

07:22.609 --> 07:23.985
Get away from me.

07:26.237 --> 07:27.989
ELYAN:
No!

07:28.156 --> 07:29.574
No!

07:37.415 --> 07:38.833
What are you doing?

07:55.225 --> 07:56.559
Nothing.

08:00.063 --> 08:02.941
[STAMMERS]
| was getting a drink of water.

08:03.108 --> 08:05.235
Tripped over the table.

08:05.402 --> 08:07.529
Uh-huh. Heh.

08:09.823 --> 08:11.366
We missed you at the tavern earlier.

08:11.533 --> 08:14.035
Percival broke Sir Brennis's wrist
in an arm-wrestle.

08:14.411 --> 08:16.788
-Sounds like fun.
-Not for Sir Brennis.

08:17.539 --> 08:18.832
Get some rest.

08:18.999 --> 08:21.001
Arthur's planned a training session
in the morning.

08:21.167 --> 08:23.461
You know how the king likes his training.

08:24.254 --> 08:25.714
Good night.

08:58.246 --> 08:59.789
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

09:02.876 --> 09:04.669
Oh, I'm sorry. I didn't mean to scare you.

09:05.336 --> 09:07.130
You didn't scare me. I was asleep.

09:09.591 --> 09:11.718
Why have you got that stupid smile
on your face?

09:11.885 --> 09:14.721
It's nothing. Why were you sleeping
with your head on the table?

09:15.847 --> 09:19.100
- I fell asleep while I was reading.
-What were you reading?

09:23.271 --> 09:26.900
| am the king of Camelot.
| do not have to answer to the likes of you.

09:27.067 --> 09:28.193
Oh, you're in a good mood.

09:28.359 --> 09:30.737
You obviously got out
of the wrong side of the table.

09:30.904 --> 09:32.655
[LAUGHING]

09:33.990 --> 09:37.410
The wrong side of the bed,
but you slept on the table, so--

09:37.577 --> 09:40.789
That's extremely clever and funny, Merlin.
There really are no limits to your wit.

09:40.955 --> 09:42.874
Now, will you please just get me
some breakfast.

09:43.041 --> 09:44.292
Right.

09:57.555 --> 09:59.682
Merlin!

10:04.646 --> 10:08.149
Pair off. Concentrate on counter-cutting.

10:08.316 --> 10:10.610
Gwaine, you're with me.
What's that in your hair?

10:12.570 --> 10:15.240
-It's stew.
-Why have you got stew in your hair?

10:16.282 --> 10:17.659
Because he was reading.

10:20.161 --> 10:23.498
Change of plan.
| think we'll try something different.

10:39.806 --> 10:41.182
[GROANING]

10:50.191 --> 10:51.609
Elyan.

11:08.668 --> 11:10.170
[MERLIN SHOUTS]

11:12.213 --> 11:13.965
Elyan.

11:18.887 --> 11:22.515
Elyan. I think he's had enough.

11:27.937 --> 11:29.606
Are you all right down there, Merlin?

11:31.274 --> 11:32.734
-Ugh...
-Good.

11:35.320 --> 11:38.156
Well, Merlin will feel that
in his arms tomorrow.

11:38.323 --> 11:41.242
All this training. When are we going
to see some real action?

11:41.409 --> 11:42.660
[WATER DRIPPING]

11:44.454 --> 11:45.747
[CHATTERING]

11:49.417 --> 11:50.710
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

12:00.929 --> 12:03.473
No. No, no.

12:05.308 --> 12:07.143
You all right?

12:11.397 --> 12:13.483
Leave me alone!

12:14.651 --> 12:16.194
Watch yourself.

12:25.536 --> 12:27.121
Elyan.

12:28.915 --> 12:30.708
Elyan. Elyan!

12:35.588 --> 12:39.425
-Why doesn't he speak?
- I don't know. It's strange.

12:39.592 --> 12:41.427
It's like he's lost his mind.

12:41.594 --> 12:44.889
When I want your medical opinion,
Gwaine, I'll ask for it.

12:45.056 --> 12:48.101
Perhaps you would leave me alone
to treat my patient.

12:50.186 --> 12:54.190
It would be better
if Arthur didn't know of this.

12:54.357 --> 12:55.942
Why do you want to keep it from Arthur?

12:57.068 --> 12:58.569
Elyan hasn't been himself recently.

12:58.736 --> 13:03.616
He hasn't said anything, but he's clearly upset
about his sister's banishment.

13:03.783 --> 13:06.452
Yes, it must have been hard for him
to see that happen to Gwen.

13:06.619 --> 13:09.831
We wouldn't want Arthur to think
that Elyan's loyalties are divided.

13:10.999 --> 13:15.378
Well, I'm sure the king doesn't have to know
about every accident that happens in Camelot.

13:16.087 --> 13:17.964
-Thank you, Gaius.
-Thank you.

13:23.845 --> 13:25.847
Elyan, can you hear me?

13:30.101 --> 13:31.894
Blink if you can hear me.

14:19.275 --> 14:23.571
Would you like me to make up the bed, sire,
or will you be sleeping on the table again?

14:32.288 --> 14:33.998
Is this about Gwen?

14:37.210 --> 14:38.961
We all miss her.

14:40.671 --> 14:42.882
-You more than anyone.
-You can go now.

14:43.841 --> 14:45.885
-Arthur--
-Get out.

14:53.643 --> 14:55.520
[DOOR CLOSES]

14:57.563 --> 15:00.525
I'm done trying to be nice to Arthur.

15:00.691 --> 15:02.860
| cook. I clean. I'm always there for him...

15:03.027 --> 15:06.614
...not to mention that small matter of saving
his life more times than I care to remember.

15:06.781 --> 15:08.825
Do I get any thanks? No.

15:08.991 --> 15:10.827
All he ever does is shout at me.

15:13.496 --> 15:16.040
So now you're ignoring me. Great.
| might as well not even exist.

15:16.207 --> 15:19.293
Hello. My name's Merlin.
But don't worry about me. I'm not even here.

15:19.460 --> 15:24.715
| fear we may have more important things
to worry about than Arthur shouting at you.

15:25.091 --> 15:26.175
What is it?

15:26.342 --> 15:30.555
Did Elyan disturb anything
yesterday at the shrine?

15:32.723 --> 15:34.100
I'm not sure.

15:34.267 --> 15:36.477
- I need you to be sure, Merlin.
- I don't know.

15:36.644 --> 15:38.855
He may have. I tried to warn them.
You know what they're like.

15:39.021 --> 15:40.773
-They don't listen.
-I'm sorry, Merlin.

15:40.940 --> 15:42.859
It's just that I'm deeply concerned for Elyan.

15:43.025 --> 15:45.319
He hasn't spoken a word
since he regained consciousness...

15:45.486 --> 15:48.531
...and I can find no physical symptoms
to explain it.

15:48.698 --> 15:53.244
The only thing I could find was a pile of salt
at the foot of his bed.

15:55.455 --> 15:58.082
-Oh, no.
-What is it, Merlin?

15:58.624 --> 16:00.835
He's trying to ward off an evil spirit.

16:01.711 --> 16:04.589
With a pile of salt? That's utter nonsense.

16:04.755 --> 16:06.132
Elyan believes it to be true.

16:08.176 --> 16:09.343
[SIGHS]

16:09.510 --> 16:14.348
Then I fear that Elyan may have
disturbed the spirit at the shrine.

16:15.475 --> 16:17.018
What?

16:18.060 --> 16:22.064
-What will that do to him?
- Idread to think what horror it might unleash.

16:22.231 --> 16:24.400
You must tell Arthur
what happened at the shrine.

16:24.567 --> 16:27.945
You must tell him that Elyan is possessed.

16:28.279 --> 16:30.740
Well, I'm not sure he'll believe me.
Not in the mood he's in.

16:30.907 --> 16:33.034
You must make him believe you.

16:43.628 --> 16:45.213
[WATER DRIPPING]

16:51.594 --> 16:53.012
[WHIMPERING]

16:53.930 --> 16:55.765
Leave me alone!

16:57.558 --> 17:00.019
Please don't be angry with me.

17:06.901 --> 17:08.361
I'm sorry.

17:27.755 --> 17:31.342
It's all right. Don't be scared.

17:39.350 --> 17:41.185
You're so cold.

17:47.066 --> 17:48.484
It's all right.

17:58.536 --> 18:00.663
What do you want from me?

18:01.747 --> 18:03.374
| want you to bring me peace.

18:04.250 --> 18:07.128
You must right the wrong
that was done to me.

18:08.296 --> 18:09.672
How?

18:10.131 --> 18:13.342
-What should I do?
-It's easy.

18:15.219 --> 18:17.555
You must kill the king.

18:46.792 --> 18:48.377
Elyan, you startled me.

18:48.961 --> 18:50.421
Is everything all right?

18:55.676 --> 18:57.637
What the hell do you think you're doing?

19:04.143 --> 19:05.603
Guards!

19:19.700 --> 19:21.369
| know Elyan is a friend to some of you...

19:21.535 --> 19:24.622
...but that friendship ended
when he tried to kill the king.

19:24.789 --> 19:27.083
Do not let him escape. Now go find him!

19:31.545 --> 19:34.632
-What happened?
-Elyan. He attacked me.

19:35.716 --> 19:37.677
| think he's possessed.

19:37.843 --> 19:39.345
What do you mean possessed?

19:39.512 --> 19:41.972
He may have disturbed a spirit at the shrine.

19:42.139 --> 19:43.849
| think that spirit's possessing him.

19:46.519 --> 19:47.853
Why else would he attack you?

19:48.604 --> 19:51.399
When we catch him,
| intend to ask him that very question.

19:53.025 --> 19:55.903
| never thought I'd see the day
when we would be hunting one of our own.

19:56.070 --> 19:57.863
| can't understand
why he would attack Arthur.

19:58.030 --> 20:00.366
What would you do if your sister
had been banished?

20:00.533 --> 20:04.161
Well, my sister is an evil old toad,
so I'd be eternally grateful.

20:04.328 --> 20:05.871
There he is!

20:22.596 --> 20:24.640
Elyan, we don't want to hurt you.

20:25.141 --> 20:26.142
Put the knife down.

20:26.308 --> 20:31.355
Why don't we all just put our weapons down
and sort this out like friends?

20:43.701 --> 20:45.828
| had to do it.

20:46.746 --> 20:48.414
Of course you did.

20:50.291 --> 20:51.917
We understand.

20:53.461 --> 20:55.171
We're your friends.

21:33.417 --> 21:35.252
You failed me.

21:35.419 --> 21:37.046
I'm sorry.

21:38.380 --> 21:40.299
I'm so sorry.

21:43.010 --> 21:45.846
AGRAVAINE: Elyan must be tried and punished
in accordance with our laws.

21:46.013 --> 21:47.932
-That would mean putting him to death.
-So be it.

21:48.098 --> 21:49.683
You can't afford to show favoritism.

21:49.850 --> 21:52.895
What if Elyan wasn't acting
of his own volition?

21:53.646 --> 21:54.730
What do you mean?

21:54.897 --> 21:58.859
Merlin believes that Elyan has been possessed
by some kind of spirit.

21:59.026 --> 22:03.239
Oh, I have no doubt he's just trying
to protect his friend.

22:04.657 --> 22:07.117
Why else would Elyan attack Arthur?

22:07.660 --> 22:10.830
His motive is obvious. He seeks revenge.

22:10.996 --> 22:13.332
You banished his sister from Camelot.

22:13.499 --> 22:14.583
MERLIN:
| know Elyan.

22:14.750 --> 22:18.295
And no matter what he feels about his sister,
he would never attack Arthur.

22:18.462 --> 22:21.632
Arthur, you must see.
All this talk of possession and spirits...

22:21.799 --> 22:23.425
...it's just a ruse to save Elyan's neck.

22:23.592 --> 22:27.221
But what if it is true?
I'd be executing an innocent man.

22:27.388 --> 22:29.306
More than that, I'd be executing a friend.

22:29.473 --> 22:33.477
You cannot be seen to allow someone to try
and kill you and then escape punishment.

22:33.644 --> 22:35.771
You will appear weak.

22:35.938 --> 22:37.857
That puts the whole of Camelot in peril.

22:39.775 --> 22:41.944
-Arthur--
-Leave me.

22:45.656 --> 22:47.241
Both of you.

22:55.708 --> 22:57.877
Agravaine is just pushing
for Elyan's execution.

22:58.043 --> 23:00.963
Arthur may have no choice
but to sentence Elyan to death.

23:01.130 --> 23:04.758
-We can't allow that to happen.
-What do you propose we do, Merlin?

23:05.342 --> 23:08.178
There must be a way of ridding Elyan
of the spirit that possesses him.

23:08.345 --> 23:10.264
It would require very powerful magic.

23:10.431 --> 23:12.433
Then I must master it
if I'm to save Elyan's life.

23:12.600 --> 23:14.852
And you intend to expel the spirit
in the cells...

23:15.394 --> 23:17.396
...under the noses of the guards?

23:17.563 --> 23:20.983
Of course not. First we need
to break Elyan out of the cells.

23:21.150 --> 23:24.069
-Did I miss out on that part?
-Ha-ha-ha.

23:32.411 --> 23:35.080
Elyan will have to be unconscious
when you expel the spirit.

23:35.247 --> 23:37.750
| put a powerful sedative in this water.

23:37.917 --> 23:40.920
And, Merlin, remember, Elyan is not himself.

23:41.086 --> 23:43.505
You cannot trust him.

23:43.672 --> 23:45.090
| know.

24:01.690 --> 24:04.276
[SPEAKING MAGIC WORDS]

24:22.211 --> 24:23.504
[SPEAKING MAGIC WORDS]

24:28.509 --> 24:30.386
[KEYS JANGLING]

24:33.013 --> 24:34.014
Merlin.

24:34.181 --> 24:36.558
| don't have time to explain.
You have to trust me.

24:51.281 --> 24:52.866
[BELLS TOLLING]

25:03.085 --> 25:05.504
We need to make it
to the cover of the woods.

25:15.431 --> 25:16.765
[BOTH PANTING]

25:19.268 --> 25:23.522
You know, Merlin,
you're much braver than you look.

25:24.440 --> 25:26.275
-Are you calling me a coward?
-Ha, ha.

25:27.109 --> 25:30.112
I'm saying there's not many people
with the courage...

25:30.279 --> 25:32.656
-...to break someone out of the cells.
- I had to do it.

25:32.823 --> 25:34.116
They were going to execute you.

25:35.743 --> 25:38.120
| know that you would never hurt Arthur...

25:38.287 --> 25:40.330
...not of your own volition.

25:44.126 --> 25:46.545
After all that running, you must be thirsty.

25:59.558 --> 26:02.561
Where are my manners?
You must be thirsty too.

26:02.728 --> 26:04.605
-No. After you.
-No, no. After you.

26:06.523 --> 26:07.816
| insist.

26:08.567 --> 26:09.777
No. I had some water earlier.

26:09.943 --> 26:13.405
If I drink too much, I have to pee all the time.
Ask Arthur. I'm always peeing.

26:14.865 --> 26:16.617
What are you looking at?

26:22.122 --> 26:23.832
I'm sorry, Merlin.

26:25.292 --> 26:26.710
For what?

26:33.467 --> 26:35.385
| won't fail you again.

26:42.059 --> 26:44.394
Just before he jumped me,
there was a presence there.

26:44.561 --> 26:46.480
| could sense it.

26:46.647 --> 26:50.776
It was Elyan who was supposed
to be knocked out. Not you, Merlin.

26:51.485 --> 26:54.154
| must find Arthur.
Elyan could make another attempt on his life.

26:54.321 --> 26:56.990
After Elyan's escape,
Arthur was put under heavy guard.

26:57.157 --> 26:59.284
There's little more you can do
to protect him.

27:01.453 --> 27:05.165
This shrine,
do you think you could find it again?

27:07.084 --> 27:09.837
I'm not sure I want to.
You said I was never to go there again.

27:12.047 --> 27:14.133
We have to find out all we can
about this spirit.

27:14.299 --> 27:19.096
Unless we know what we're dealing with,
we won't be able to help Elyan or Arthur.

27:34.820 --> 27:36.321
Merlin?

27:39.366 --> 27:41.410
It's just through these trees.

27:54.798 --> 27:56.383
What are we looking for?

27:57.885 --> 27:59.595
I'm not entirely sure.

27:59.970 --> 28:04.641
But remember, don't disturb anything.

28:04.808 --> 28:06.685
Trust me. I won't.

28:18.989 --> 28:20.490
[WOOD CRACKS]

28:21.658 --> 28:22.993
Sorry.

28:25.662 --> 28:26.955
[VOICES WHISPERING]

28:29.291 --> 28:30.542
[WATER TRICKLING]

28:42.638 --> 28:44.431
[CHILD CRYING]

28:56.985 --> 28:58.862
[CHILDREN SCREAMING]

29:02.491 --> 29:03.867
[MAN SHOUTING]

29:04.326 --> 29:05.911
Gaius!

29:06.078 --> 29:07.079
[VOICES STOP]

29:07.246 --> 29:09.122
What is it, Merlin?

29:10.040 --> 29:11.541
[GROANING]

29:20.634 --> 29:23.095
Something terrible happened here.

29:27.099 --> 29:30.018
These runes are in the druid tongue.

29:30.185 --> 29:35.190
| also found this. There are crossbow bolts
scattered all around.

29:37.818 --> 29:40.028
This was Uther's doing, wasn't it?

29:41.405 --> 29:46.368
It is revenge for Uther's crime
that the spirit seeks.

29:53.041 --> 29:54.793
[DOOR OPENS]

29:56.128 --> 29:58.797
Merlin. Good of you to join me.

29:58.964 --> 30:02.634
Perhaps I should fill you in on all
that's been happening while you've been--

30:02.801 --> 30:05.304
That's a good question.
What the hell have you been doing?

30:06.722 --> 30:10.058
-I was--
-Choose your next words carefully.

30:10.559 --> 30:11.977
They may be your last.

30:12.144 --> 30:14.771
| was searching in the woods
for some herbs for Gaius.

30:14.938 --> 30:19.359
Very rare herbs. Hard to find, actually,
and I got lost--

30:19.526 --> 30:23.947
You mean to tell me that you've been
wandering around in the woods all night?

30:24.114 --> 30:25.157
Yes.

30:25.782 --> 30:27.367
What happened to your head?

30:28.493 --> 30:30.704
I-- I tripped over a root...

30:30.871 --> 30:33.373
...and I hit my head on a tree
and I knocked myself out.

30:33.540 --> 30:35.208
[CHUCKLES]

30:35.751 --> 30:39.212
Hmm. Well, after wandering around
in the woods all night...

30:39.379 --> 30:42.466
...knocking yourself out,
you must be hungry.

30:42.841 --> 30:46.053
-I'm starving.
-Pull up a chair. Tuck in.

30:46.595 --> 30:49.473
Oh, thanks very much. I am actually--
You're joking.

31:28.512 --> 31:30.555
Oh, no.

31:38.730 --> 31:39.981
[RUSTLING]

31:55.831 --> 31:57.207
Why are you doing this?

32:01.586 --> 32:03.922
[AS BOY]
| must avenge my death.

32:06.883 --> 32:08.260
What have you done to Elyan?

32:23.442 --> 32:24.526
MERLIN:
Arthur!

32:26.611 --> 32:29.322
Don't make me Kill you.
| don't want to kill you.

32:44.337 --> 32:47.174
Stop! That's not the Elyan we know!

33:08.653 --> 33:09.988
You let him go.

33:13.867 --> 33:17.245
AGRAVAINE: The palace is secure.
No one is able to get in or out.

33:17.412 --> 33:19.581
And we're searching the lower town
even as I speak.

33:20.415 --> 33:23.960
Fear not, my lord.
Elyan will be hunted down and slain.

33:24.127 --> 33:26.588
I'll see to it personally.

33:26.755 --> 33:28.465
ARTHUR:
Thank you, Uncle.

33:33.803 --> 33:37.015
You know that isn't Elyan,
or you wouldn't have let him go.

33:39.017 --> 33:42.604
When Elyan spoke to me,
it wasn't with his voice.

33:44.523 --> 33:46.191
It was the voice of a boy, a child.

33:46.358 --> 33:49.277
That is the voice of the spirit
that now possesses him.

33:50.737 --> 33:52.864
What do you know about this shrine, Gaius?

33:53.031 --> 33:55.659
| believe the site was once a druid camp.

33:55.825 --> 33:58.578
There is evidence
that the camp was attacked.

33:59.746 --> 34:02.958
Your father was relentless
in his persecution of the druids.

34:03.416 --> 34:05.252
Many died.

34:05.418 --> 34:09.839
| believe it is one of those tormented souls
that now possesses Elyan.

34:14.302 --> 34:16.513
And that's why he seeks his revenge.

34:16.679 --> 34:19.431
The spirit craves peace.

34:19.599 --> 34:22.643
He wishes to find his proper place
in the other world...

34:22.811 --> 34:27.065
...but the unjust nature of his death
has denied him that.

34:29.192 --> 34:31.444
Is there anything that can be done
to change this?

34:31.610 --> 34:35.489
In druid lore, only the atonement
of the perpetrator...

34:36.116 --> 34:38.784
...can bring the spirit peace.

34:38.952 --> 34:40.370
MERLIN:
Uther's dead.

34:42.205 --> 34:44.291
-He can't atone for what he did.
GAIUS: Indeed.

34:44.456 --> 34:46.042
What about Elyan?

34:46.543 --> 34:48.503
Elyan is no longer the man you knew.

34:49.212 --> 34:52.841
The spirit has a hold over him
that may be too powerful to break.

34:53.007 --> 34:57.387
All we can hope is that he'll be found
before he has a chance to enact his revenge.

34:59.639 --> 35:01.182
And if we do find him?

35:03.226 --> 35:07.314
Then I fear you have no choice
but to kill him.

35:24.164 --> 35:28.209
It's not your fault. You can't be held
responsible for everything your father did.

35:31.796 --> 35:33.465
That will be all, Merlin. Thank you.

35:34.716 --> 35:36.509
Are you sure you don't want me to stay?

35:38.053 --> 35:40.096
| think I'm going to get an early night.

35:41.306 --> 35:45.685
Yeah. Yeah, I'm pretty tired too,
what with having spent the night in the woods.

35:45.852 --> 35:49.439
No one said anything about you getting
an early night, Merlin.

35:49.606 --> 35:54.152
In fact, you can make up for your
little escapade by polishing my armor.

36:05.038 --> 36:06.581
[SIGHS]

37:03.888 --> 37:05.432
ARTHUR:
Merlin.

37:07.100 --> 37:08.351
Fancy meeting you here.

37:08.518 --> 37:10.812
What the hell are you doing
creeping around in the woods?

37:10.979 --> 37:13.606
I'm following you. What are you doing
creeping around in the woods?

37:13.773 --> 37:16.526
-Something I should've done a long time ago.
-Elyan could be out here.

37:16.693 --> 37:18.611
Do you know how dangerous that is?

37:18.778 --> 37:20.488
| have to face him.

37:21.823 --> 37:24.701
Feel free to go back to Camelot
anytime you like.

37:30.081 --> 37:31.875
You're not going back then?

37:32.667 --> 37:34.586
| thought I might tag along.

37:34.753 --> 37:36.713
| don't want you getting lost and scared.

37:48.683 --> 37:50.810
Are you sure you want to do this?

37:52.854 --> 37:55.273
Maybe we should wait until it's light.

37:57.650 --> 38:00.069
Or we could just do it now,
whatever it is that we're doing...

38:00.236 --> 38:03.656
...in the dark, when it's incredibly scary
and dangerous.

38:24.177 --> 38:26.763
Is that a good idea?
We might be needing it.

38:28.056 --> 38:30.850
I'm not sure a sword will be
much use against a spirit.

38:31.017 --> 38:32.977
What about against Elyan?

38:35.939 --> 38:37.524
I'm here!

38:39.359 --> 38:40.902
That's what you want, isn't it?

38:41.069 --> 38:42.862
What are you doing?

38:46.533 --> 38:50.203
Everything Gaius said about this place
is right except for one thing.

38:51.329 --> 38:55.458
It wasn't my father that led the raid
on the druid camp.

38:56.793 --> 38:58.169
| did.

39:07.846 --> 39:10.223
[AS BOY]
My blood is on your hands.

39:11.975 --> 39:15.144
| cannot rest because of what you did.

39:17.689 --> 39:19.023
| know.

39:28.700 --> 39:31.661
| am responsible for what happened to you...

39:32.537 --> 39:34.622
...and for all the violence
that happened here.

39:36.666 --> 39:42.171
When I led the attack on your camp,
| was young and inexperienced.

39:43.381 --> 39:47.635
| was desperate to prove myself
to my men, to my father.

39:52.807 --> 39:54.767
| told the men to spare
the women and children...

39:54.934 --> 39:57.228
...but I know that some of them
ignored the order.

39:57.395 --> 39:59.355
And there was so much happening.

40:00.148 --> 40:01.858
| wanted to stop it.

40:03.943 --> 40:05.570
| froze.

40:06.738 --> 40:08.781
| didn't know what to do.

40:17.415 --> 40:19.208
| can still hear the screams.

40:24.380 --> 40:26.424
| cannot right this wrong.

40:26.591 --> 40:30.386
Nothing I can do will ever change the horrors
that happened that day.

40:34.599 --> 40:37.727
But I can promise that now that I am king...

40:37.894 --> 40:41.064
...will do everything that I can...

40:41.230 --> 40:44.275
...to prevent anything like this
ever happening again.

40:47.528 --> 40:49.197
From this day forth...

40:50.031 --> 40:52.700
...the druid people will be treated
with the respect they deserve.

40:52.867 --> 40:54.702
| give you my word.

41:04.963 --> 41:08.716
| am truly sorry for what happened to you.

41:10.343 --> 41:11.636
[GRUNTS THEN PANTING]

41:40.623 --> 41:42.458
| forgive you.

42:21.789 --> 42:23.291
ELYAN [IN NORMAL VOICE]:
Arthur?

42:39.891 --> 42:41.225
[BELLS TOLLING]

42:48.775 --> 42:50.568
How's Elyan? Is he going to be all right?

42:50.735 --> 42:53.571
Gaius says he's going to make
a full recovery.

42:57.366 --> 43:01.079
You know, that was incredibly moving
what you said at the shrine.

43:02.622 --> 43:05.166
As long as Elyan's going to be all right,
it served its purpose.

43:05.333 --> 43:07.919
It wasn't just about Elyan though, was it?

43:08.086 --> 43:09.420
You meant it.

43:10.171 --> 43:12.090
- I know you did.
-Does this have a point, Merlin?

43:13.466 --> 43:16.344
| don't think I've ever seen you cry before,
not like that.

43:16.511 --> 43:18.387
You had tears running down your cheeks.

43:18.554 --> 43:21.265
It's nice to see this new sensitive,
emotional side to you.

43:21.432 --> 43:23.768
- It suits you.
-Shut up, Merlin.

43:23.935 --> 43:26.521
Ah, I really thought you'd changed.

43:28.564 --> 43:30.358
Then you're as stupid as you are ugly.

43:35.863 --> 43:38.658
So there's no chance
that we could have a hug?

43:45.873 --> 43:47.125
[MERLIN GROANS]

43:47.291 --> 43:49.168
MALE VOICE:
Merlin.

43:50.253 --> 43:52.046
Princess Mithian, you are most welcome.

43:52.213 --> 43:53.673
[BOTH LAUGHING]

43:53.840 --> 43:56.676
It's Arthur's fate to marry Gwen.
Am I supposed to do anything about it?

43:56.843 --> 44:00.012
Guinevere made her choice.
Now she must take the consequences.

44:00.179 --> 44:02.056
GWEN:
They're planning to attack Camelot.

44:02.223 --> 44:05.143
MORGANA: Who is this woman?
MAN: A wench I recently acquired. No more.

44:05.309 --> 44:06.811
MORGANA:
We must find her now.

44:06.978 --> 44:08.938
-If you stay here--
- I have what I deserve.

44:09.105 --> 44:11.566
MORGANA: You wish to see
your beloved Arthur again?

44:11.732 --> 44:13.192
Then so you shall.

44:13.359 --> 44:14.610
[SCREAMING]

45:00.781 --> 45:01.782
[English - US - SDH]
